{"abstract": "The one drawback for Procter & Gamble is that it is losing a longtime shareholder, Robert Cyran and Kevin Allison of Reuters Breakingviews write.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/11/13/both-sides-gain-in-berkshire-duracell-deal/", "snippet": "The one drawback for Procter & Gamble is that it is losing a longtime shareholder, Robert Cyran and Kevin Allison of Reuters Breakingviews write.", "lead_paragraph": "Warren E. Buffett\u2019s multibillion-dollar deal for Duracell is more positive than negative. Berkshire Hathaway is paying for its latest acquisition by trading its stake in Procter & Gamble, valued at $4.7 billion, for the consumer stalwart\u2019s battery unit. Swapping a reliable staple for a declining business looks odd. But the transaction is structured in a way that means both sides are getting a decent deal.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/11/14/business/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 411, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/11/14/business/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 411}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/11/14/business/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews-jumbo.jpg", "height": 701, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/11/14/business/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews/dbpix-buffett-breakingviews-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1403, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "ur